  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Ezekiel 22:2-5",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezekiel 22:2-5",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Wilt thou judge, wilt thou judge the bloody city? — Wilt thou plead ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for it? Or rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Wilt thou not judge? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "see note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 20:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The expression is doubled to awaken the prophet more fully, and to quicken him to his work. Jerusalem is termed ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the bloody city, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "עיר הדמים",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the city of bloods, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "because of the blood of innocent persons, of children sacrificed to Moloch, and of prophets and righteous men shed in her, and that by courts of justice under colour of law. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Yea, thou shalt show her — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Make her know; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "all her abominations — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That I may be justified in all the desolations which I have brought, and shall still more fully bring upon her. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The city sheddeth blood in the midst of it — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Openly and impudently; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that her time may come — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The time of her destruction, as the consequence of her having filled up the measure of her iniquities; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and maketh idols against herself — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To her own ruin. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Thou hast caused thy days to draw near — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The days of thy sorrows and sufferings; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and art come even to thy years — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To the end of thy years of trial, so that thou shalt be borne with no longer. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Therefore have I made thee a reproach unto the heathen — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Have exposed thee to their contempt and scorn; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and a mocking to all countries — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "proverb, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "by-word, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and cause of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "astonishment ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to all people, according to the prediction of Moses, (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 28:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) and the solemn warning given by the Lord to Solomon, when he appeared to him after the dedication of the temple, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 9:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Those that are near — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And are eye-witnesses of thy apostacy and degeneracy, as the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Edomites, Ammonites, Moabites, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Philistines; and those that be far from thee — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Medes, Persians, Hyrcanians, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c., to whom thou shalt be carried captive; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shall mock thee, which art infamous — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Of a most infamous name; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and much vexed — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Afflicted, empoverished, and ruined: or rather, who art ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "full of tumult ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "trouble, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "רבת המהומה",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " more properly signifies: that is, in which there are continually confusion and disorder, by the commission of acts of violence.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "22:1-16 The prophet is to judge the bloody city; the city of bloods. Jerusalem is so called, because of her crimes. The sins which Jerusalem stands charged with, are exceeding sinful. Murder, idolatry, disobedience to parents, oppression and extortion, profanation of the sabbath and holy things, seventh commandment sins, lewdness and adultery. Unmindfulness of God was at the bottom of all this wickedness. Sinners provoke God because they forget him. Jerusalem has filled the measure of her sins. Those who give up themselves to be ruled by their lusts, will justly be given up to be portioned by them. Those who resolve to be their own masters, let them expect no other happiness than their own hands can furnish; and a miserable portion it will prove.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The fourth word of judgment ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 22:1-16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The sins which have brought ruin upon Jerusalem are the sins which disgraced the pagan inhabitants of Canaan, whom the Israelites were to cast out (compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The commission of like sins would insure like judgment. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. See Eze 20:4; that is, \"Wilt thou not judge?\" &c. (compare Eze 23:36).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the bloody city—literally, \"the city of bloods\"; so called on account of murders perpetrated in her, and sacrifices of children to Molech (Eze 22:3, 4, 6, 9; 24:6, 9).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Some would have the prophet here to be questioned, whether he would, and why he would, plead for such a city. Others, that God doth forbid him to plead for it, or be solicitous about it. I rather think God doth awake: him to more vigorous reproving of this sinful people, and threatening them for sin. The question is doubled to awaken the prophet more fully, and to quicken him to his work. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "The bloody city; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Jerusalem, which is guilty of the murders of innocent ones, of prophets and holy men. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Show her; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " make her know, at least tell her by writing; for the prophet was at Babylon now, and could not speak to then at Jerusalem, but he might and must send word to then what their abominations were. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "All her abominations; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " all the kinds, not all individual acts of them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
